title: Chelsea sweat over Reece James as he pulls out of England U21 duty after suffering injury setback
text:
Chelsea duo Reece James and Trevoh Chalobah have withdrawn from the England Under-21 squad because of injury.

The FA have confirmed that Aidy Boothroyd will be without the players for the matches against Slovenia and Austria.

Full back James will now return to Stamford Bridge, where he has just returned from an ankle injury that he picked up while on international duty with Aidy Boothroyd's men during the summer.

Chelsea defender Reece James has been withdrawn as a precaution after suffering injury

The pair were withdrawn as a precaution and James is expected to report for training at Cobham next week.

James has been an unused substitute for the last two Premier League games after making his comeback in the Carabao Cup win over Grimsby Town last month.

Midfielder Chalobah, on loan at Champioship side Huddersfield, took knocks against both Stoke City and Hull City and has been ruled out of Friday's friendly against Slovenia, which is a warm-up for next Tuesday's European Championship qualifier against Austria at Milton Keynes.
description: Chelsea duo Reece James and Trevoh Chalobah have withdrawn from the England U21 squad because of injury.
